Let \emph{L} be the line which is parallel to the plane

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}2x+y-z=5
\end{align*}

and perpendicular to the line

\begin{align*}
x=3-t\qquad{}y=1-2t\qquad{}z=3t.
\end{align*}

Find parametric equations for the line \emph{L} if \emph{L} passes
through a point Q(a,b,c) where a\textless{}0, b\textgreater{}0,
c\textgreater{}0 and the distances from Q to the xy-plane, xz-plane, and
the yz-plane are 2, 3, and 4 respectively.
